INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (1486,'Scott Bronson\n\nBoston, MA<br>\nirc: bronson<br>\nemail: <Email>bronson@rinspin.com</Email>\n\nHow I\'ve helped OZ: installed this wiki and help maintain it.  Also, a very long time ago I submitted a patch to fix the Opie Pacman game.  :)\n\n== Equipment ==\n\n* Zaurus [[SL-5500]] obtained through the [http://www.linuxdevices.com/news/NS4241298322.html Home Shopping Network blowout].\n* D-Link DCF-660W 802.11 Compact Flash card.\n* 256 MB SanDisk SD Card\n\n== Hardware Thoughts == \n\nI normally run the 64/0 image.  The 16 MB flash in the device is way too small, but I don\'t like trying to decide where to install apps, and having them disappear when I eject the SD card.  Also, my SD card is damned slow.  I wish wish WISH this device had 32 MB flash.\n\nThe screen is too damn narrow for browsing the web.  It\'s barely liveable if you rotate the screen and use the device sideways.  I don\'t care how high the screen is, just give me width!\n\n== GPE Thoughts ==\n\nOpie is a far more polished environment.  That said, I like GPE better.  GPE feels more like it\'s more a part of the Linux desktop.  Opie feels somewhat like a one-off hack.  That\'s just my opinion, of course.\n\nSome issues:\n\n* Why does a tap-longtap scroll a scroll bar to the extreme end?  This makes it damned hard to scroll line-by-line.  It\'s lika tap-tap-tap tap-damn where was I?  Its painful.  If I want to go to the bottom, I\'ll just drag the scroll bar thumb thank you very much.  (this awful behavior smells intentional because it seems like the device would have to go out of its way to do this...)\n\n* It\'s really strange that there\'s no active task switcher. I would expect a submenu in the Start menu or a task menu applet. Or both. Instead, you can sometimes click on the window\'s title bar.  How am I supposed to discover that??\n\n* Window titlebars take up a lot of room and really don\'t offer much functionality that I can tell.  The panel, on the other hand, is always overflowing with icons.  How about allowing us to place applets on the outsides of the window title bar?\n\n* interactive-help: useless, hopeless, a waste of space!\n** useless: couldn\'t find anything that actually offered help\n** hopeless: there is no way you\'re going to add help for everything that the user can click on.  It\'s much better\n** waste of space: the panel on a portrait Z doesn\'t have much room for icons.  And certainly it has no room for an icon this useless.\n** What\'s worse than not having a help button?  Having a help button that is totally and utterly unhelpful.\n\n* I\'ve seen a tiny analog clock in GPE screenshots.  Where can I obtain this?  Solve the width and rotation issues in one blow.\n\n* gpe-aerial:\n** Should take over the function of the wireless monitor.\n** Should display your current settings when you click on it\n** Shoulw have an \"associate with other networks\" button that would bring up the network switcher.\n\n* Panel doesn\'t handle rotation very well.  Especially the alarm clock changing its size.  Panel Manager should allow you to add and remove panel apps too.\n: Remove: just add an X right below the ^ and v arrows.\n: Add: make another list of the apps available to add.\n\n* Should add a battery graph to the CPU/mem monitor.  Ideally, whould make configurable which bars are shown in the panel.  Then the window that comes up would show all the bars, with labels.\n** network bandwidth\n** Disk space\n** temperature?\n\n* Package Manager\n** Should show progress monitor in dialog on startup.\n** Should quit entirely if startup window is closed.  As it is, it looks like it should work... but quits the minute you click on something.\n** Should display a description of the pack','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (1487,'This page lists the user pages of OpenZaurus Wiki members.  Please create a user page and add yourself to this list.  [[user page|How to create a user page]].\n\n* [[User:Bronson]]: Scott Bronson\n\nA list of all users on this wiki can be found [[Special:Listusers|here]].','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (1488,'A user page is a location for your random thoughts about OpenZaurus.\n\nYou must first create an account to give yourself a user page.  Log in and click on your name to edit it.\n\nIt is helpful to add contact information but certainly not required.  It is also nice to include the hardware and accessories you\'re currently using OpenZaurus on.\n\nYou can obfuscate your email address so that spammers will have a hard time harvesting it: <Email>addr@example.com</Email>\n\n    &lt;email&gt;addr@example.com&lt;email&gt;\n\nOnce you are happy with your page, add it to [[Users|this list]].','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (1489,'A user page is a location for your random thoughts about OpenZaurus.\n\nYou must first create an account.  Log in and click on your name in the upper-right corner.  Now click on edit.\n\nIt is helpful to add contact information but certainly not required.  You might also want to include the hardware and accessories you\'re currently using with OpenZaurus.\n\nYou can obfuscate your email address so that spammers will have a hard time harvesting it: <Email>addr@example.com</Email>\n\n    &lt;email&gt;addr@example.com&lt;email&gt;\n\nOnce you are happy with your page, add it to [[Users|this list]].','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (1490,'In a few weeks or months we might remove the link to this page from the home page.  You can always get to this page by visiting http://openzaurus.berlios.de/Admin.\n\n== Monitoring Pages ==\n\nAn RSS feed reader is the best tool to use to monitor the entire site for changes.  Simply subscribe to [http://openzaurus.berlios.de/wiki/index.php?title=Special:Recentchanges&feed=rss this url].  This is most useful for site admins.\n\nIn addition, when you create an account, you can set up your preferences so that you can be sent an email whenever a page that you have previously edited is changed.  You can also manually subscribe to individual pages.  Click on \"Create an account\" in the upper right-hand corner.  This is most useful for site contributors.\n\n== Controlling Spam ==\n\nThe wiki currently allows unregistered users to edit the site.  This helps encourage people to contribute content.  When spam becomes a problem, we will be forced to make the site more restrictive.\n\nWhen spammers hit the site, their changes are very easily reverted:\n* View the page\'s history\n* Click on the date of the page you\'d like to revert to.  This opens that revision in an edit window.\n* Ignore the warning about an out of date copy and save the page.  The spam has been eradicated.\n\n== Navigation Links ==\n\nTo change the always-visible navigation links, modify [[MediaWiki:Sidebar]].  See [[Help:Sidebar]] for more.  Only admins can edit the sidebar.  See [http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Help:User_rights wikimedia] for more information.\n\n== TODO ==\n\n* Setup automatic backups for the database and the site repo.  (what about uploaded images?)\n* Make this site respond to wiki.openzaurus.org.  Who has control over the openzaurus.org DNS?\n* Test image upload.  This is fairly low priority but might be useful.  Screenshot galleries would be especially nice.\n\nmuch later:\n\n* Incorporate the new logo\n* Ask someone to create a custom theme.  [http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/MediaWiki_look_and_feel] [http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Skins]  Look to [http://hula-project.org] or [http://www.mono-project.com/Main_Page] for inspiration.\n\n== Done ==\n\n* 13 Apr 2006: Placed site content under version control.  Subversion repo is in ~bronson/wikirepo (can\'t use BerliOS public SVN since this repo contains passwords).  Users who are part of the BerliOS openzaurus group can access it.  svn co file://localhost/home/users/bronson/wikirepo\n* 12 Apr 2006: Add a param to ignore any cached pages older than a given date. ([[ShowTimestamp]])\n* 12 Apr 2006: Get rid of index.php in the URLs (that was painful -- $wgCacheEpoch appears to be ignored?)\n\n== Tools ==\n\n[[ShowTimestamp]]\n\n== Statistics ==\n\n[http://openzaurus.berlios.de/usage/ Site Statistics]\n\n[http://openzaurus.berlios.de/info.php PHPInfo]','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (1491,'This page contains some guidelines to use when adding documentation to this site.  As long as pages follow these rules, we can maintain some consistency across the site.\n\n* It\'s \"Zauruses\", not Zaurii or other odd pluralizations.\n* Always use [[DogName]]s unless you need to make a distinction of devices in the same family.  \'\'The [[Collie]] and [[Poodle]] are Portrait Zauruses.  Of these devices, the [[SL-5000]] and [[SL-5600]] have 32 MB of RAM while the [[SL-5500]] has 64 MB.\'\'\n* [[DogName]]s and [[ModelName]]s always redirect to the appropriate page.\n: Well... it\'s not obvious to do that since dognames are not wiki words (mix of upper/lower case)... so not specially easy to type when writing inn the wiki... --[[User:OlivierBerger|OlivierBerger]] 13:14, 13 April 2006 (BST)\n: MediaWiki doesn\'t really use WikiWords anyway.  You can use <nowiki>[[brackets]]</nowiki> for each link. [[User:Bronson|Bronson]] 18:48, 13 April 2006 (BST)\n* \"Zaurus\" is always capitalized.\n\nUse proper namespaces:\n\n* /HowTo/USB_Networking\n* /HowTo/Passwordless_SSH\n* /HowTo/SomethingOther\n\n* /Docs/Something\n\nUse language code after section name:\n\n* /HowTo/DE/USB_Netzwerk\n* /HowTo/FR/Le_réseau_par_USB\n\nThe pages on this wiki should be used for professional, objective presentation of information.  Opinions and rants (within reason) are encouraged \'\'as long as\'\' they are on discussion pages or personal pages.  (create an account to obtain a personal page)','utf-8');
