inet addr:192.168.2.50  Bcast:192.168.2.255  Mask:255.255.255.0\n          UP BROADCAST RUNNING MULTICAST  MTU:1500  Metric:1\n          RX packets:3459 errors:2 dropped:2 overruns:0 frame:2\n          TX packets:251 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 carrier:0\n          collisions:0 txqueuelen:100\n\nThis does not prevent logging into the Zaurus using ssh but does prevent downloading files larger than about 1kB.  I am not sure why this happens, it may be related to [http://bugzilla.kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=5744 this kernel bug report]\n\nThe solution is to reduce the MTU on the Zaurus end.  You can configure the Zaurus to do this automatically by editing /etc/network/interfaces.  Find the section starting \'iface usbd0\' and add the following line:\n\n  up ifconfig usbd0 mtu 1494 \n\n== References ==\n[http://www.linux-usb.org/usbnet The GNU Linux usbnet driver]\n\n[http://linux-net.osdl.org/index.php/Bridge Linux ethernet bridging]\n\n[http://www.gentoo.org/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=4 Gentoo network configuration]','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (1716,'I own a collie which I use as a mobile Japanese-German dictionary (with the help of wadoku and zten).  I have long wanted to replace the Sharp ROM with OZ but the lack of a Japanese input method for OZ prevented me from doing so.  Recently, it looks likely I may be able to switch.  I want to use the Z as a [http://gakusei.sf.net tool for learning Japanese], too.','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (1717,'I\'m an OpenZaurus and OpenEmbedded user living in Spain. I got my first Zaurus, a SL-5500, in Christmas 2003. I installed OpenZaurus into it and used it for a while until it suffered a tragic accident (broken touchscreen). Now I use it as a generic embedded Linux system with screen, for miscellaneous hardware projects, and meanwhile also fixed the suspend bugs in the OE kernel (because they broke my applications :)). Later on I got a SL-6000L, and I\'ve been tinkering with OpenZaurus and OpenEmbedded since.\n\nCurrent Status:\n\n- SL-5500 minus touchscreen and case: Running self-built OZ bootstrap image. Lots of wires coming out of it.\n\n<img src=\"http://marcansoft.com/subidos/images/marcan_collie_surgery.jpg\">ç\n\n\n- SL-6000L: running OpenZaurus 3.5.4 GPE','utf-8');
