INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (1759,'In a few weeks or months we might remove the link to this page from the home page.  You can always get to this page by visiting http://openzaurus.berlios.de/Admin.\n\n== Monitoring Pages ==\n\nAn RSS feed reader is the best tool to use to monitor the entire site for changes.  Simply subscribe to [http://openzaurus.berlios.de/wiki/index.php?title=Special:Recentchanges&feed=rss this url].  This is most useful for site admins.\n\nIn addition, when you create an account, you can set up your preferences so that you can be sent an email whenever a page that you have previously edited is changed.  You can also manually subscribe to individual pages.  Click on \"Create an account\" in the upper right-hand corner.  This is most useful for site contributors.\n\n== Controlling Spam ==\n\nThe wiki currently allows unregistered users to edit the site.  This helps encourage people to contribute content.  When spam becomes a problem, we will be forced to make the site more restrictive.\n\nWhen spammers hit the site, their changes are very easily reverted:\n* View the page\'s history\n* Click on the date of the page you\'d like to revert to.  This opens that revision in an edit window.\n* Ignore the warning about an out of date copy and save the page.  The spam has been eradicated.\n\n== Navigation Links ==\n\nTo change the always-visible navigation links, modify [[MediaWiki:Sidebar]].  See [[Help:Sidebar]] for more.  Only admins can edit the sidebar.  See [http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Help:User_rights wikimedia] for more information.\n\n== TODO ==\n\n\n* Get kergoth to make wiki.openzaurus.org a CNAME for www.berlios.de.  (I emailed him on 14 Apr).\n** A month later, no reply.  Is there any way to contact him other than email?\n* Add a TODO template and a skeleton template so we can keep track of the parts of the wiki that are in desperate need of attention.\n* Setup automatic backups for the database and the site repo.  (what about uploaded images?)\n* Test image upload.  This is fairly low priority but might be useful.  Screenshot galleries would be especially nice.\n\nmuch later:\n\n* Incorporate the new logo\n* Ask someone to create a custom theme.  [http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/MediaWiki_look_and_feel] [http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Skins]  Look to [http://hula-project.org] or [http://www.mono-project.com/Main_Page] for inspiration.  Ensure that the new theme is easily read on Zaruses (even 240 pix wide?)\n\n== Done ==\n\n* 14 Apr 2006: Added a [[OpenZaurus:About|Contact]] link to the sidebar.\n* 14 Apr 2006: Ensured that the BerliOS logo is displayed on every page.\n* 14 Apr 2006: Created the virtual host for wiki.openzaurus.org.  Now just need to update openzaurus.org dns...  kergoth?\n* 13 Apr 2006: Placed site content under version control.  Subversion repo is in ~bronson/wikirepo (can\'t use BerliOS public SVN since this repo contains passwords).  Users who are part of the BerliOS openzaurus group can access it.  svn co file://localhost/home/users/bronson/wikirepo\n* 12 Apr 2006: Add a param to ignore any cached pages older than a given date. ([[ShowTimestamp]])\n* 12 Apr 2006: Get rid of index.php in the URLs (that was painful -- $wgCacheEpoch appears to be ignored?)\n\n== Tools ==\n\n[[ShowTimestamp]]\n\n== Statistics ==\n\n[http://openzaurus.berlios.de/usage/ Site Statistics]\n\n[http://openzaurus.berlios.de/info.php PHPInfo]','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (1760,'\nI started with the Opie OZ image. You can likely start with the GPE image, but these instructions start from the Opie image.\n\nFlash your Zaurus with Opie. I suggest using a kernel which gives you the maximum amount of memory. I used the 64-0 image on my collie.\n\nMove your root filesystem to a linux formatted SD card (I use ext2). I used these instructions. In case that’s down, you can use the moveRootToSd.sh script (see attachments tab at top). You may not have to do this, but if you don’t you’ll likely have to install the GPE packages to your SD card or CF card and ipkg-link them.\n\nChange Opie to start on Virtual Terminal 3. Edit your /etc/init.d/opie script. Change all instances of “-terminal 2″ to “-terminal 3″. I found two of these.\n\nRestart Opie. Opie will now be on Virtual Terminal 3.\n\nSet up all of the OZ feeds in your /etc/ipkg.conf. Here are all of the ones I have:\n\nsrc e http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/e/\nsrc gnome http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/gnome/\nsrc upgrades http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/upgrades/\nsrc upgrades2 http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/upgrades/\nsrc devel http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/devel/\nsrc kernel http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/kernel/\nsrc base http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/base/\nsrc libs http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/libs/\nsrc console http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/console/\nsrc opie http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/opie\nsrc unknown http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/unknown/\nsrc gpe http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/gpe/\nsrc x11 http://openzaurus.org/official/unstable/3.5.3/feed/x11/\n\n\nNote there are a few here that don’t currently exist, but they should at some point.\n\nUpdate your package lists:\n\nipkg update\n\n\n\nInstall the packages. Due to incorrect dependencies, you’ll have to use -force-depends. You also need to install libcairo1 as the dependency doesn’t exist for it.\nMake sure that the above xserver is the right one for your Zaurus. You may need a different one depending on your model.\n\nipkg install libcairo1\nipkg install -force-depends xserver-kdrive-fbdev\nipkg install -force-depends gpe-base-depends gpe-task-base gpe-task-settings\n\n\nYou may also have to uninstall bluez-utils-nodbus for gpe-task-base to install or ipkg install -force-overwrite bluez-utils-nodbus. I don’t know what the “correct” way to do it is. I believe I forced overwriting.\n\nIf there are 404s or everything didn’t install, try running the install command again. At this point GPE will likely start up on its own, assuming everything worked. You may want to restart your Zaurus at this point. Now you should have both Opie and GPE on your Zaurus. Enjoy!\n\nThere are also a few other things I’ve added to make GPE more usable. The first allows you to switch to Opie easily from GPE.\n\nPut this in “/gotoopie.sh”.\n\n#!/bin/sh\nchvt 3\n\n\nThen put this in /usr/share/applications/goto-opie.desktop:\n\n[Desktop Entry]\nName=Goto Opie\nComment=Switch to Opie\nExec=/gotoopie.sh\nTerminal=0\nType=Application\nIcon=/opt/QtPalmtop/pics/logo/opielogo.png\nCategories=Utility;GPE\nStartupNotify=False\n\n\nGo to the Utilities group and you should now have “Goto Opie” icon.\n\nI also added a “Suspend” icon since I couldn’t find one in GPE. Put this in “/suspend.sh”:\n\n#!/bin/sh\napm -s\n\n\nThis may cause a C series Zaurus to not wake up after suspending. If this happens, try this instead:\n\n#!/bin/sh\necho 1 > /proc/sys/pm/suspend\n\n\nAnd put this in “/usr/share/applications/suspend.desktop”:\n\n[Desktop Entry]\nName=Suspend\nComment=Suspend\nExec=/suspend.sh\nTerminal=0\nType=Application\nIcon=gpe-config-sleep.png\nCategories=Utility;GPE\nStartupNotify=False\n\n\n\nYou may need to logout of GPE and log back in for the above icons to show up.\n\nPopularity: 1%\n\nPosted in misc |\n16 Responses\n\n   1. Perry Hutchison Says:\n      April 18th, 2005 at 02:36\n\n      You said that ipkg was “new and improved”, but I cannot install a single package that works. I have an SL6000 using opie image 3.5.3. I tried opie devorak, mileage 2.5, and portabase 1.9. None will run. I even tried installing mileage on a command line. It installed. but gave a symbol lookup error: undefined symbol _70String.shared_null, when runned. I am mystified.\n   2. Hrw Says:\n      April 19th, 2005 at 11:09\n\n      Perry - that message about undefined symbol means that package which you install is not from OZ (compiled for SharpROM).\n   3. lars Says:\n      April 21st, 2005 at 07:50\n\n      where can I download teh moveRootToSd.sh script?\n   4. Hrw Says:\n      April 22nd, 2005 at 09:07\n\n      lars: search for “rboot” scripts.\n   5. lars Says:\n      April 22nd, 2005 at 13:02\n\n      Hrw: Thank You, I’ve found it.\n   6. Ben Johnson Says:\n      April 25th, 2005 at 19:40\n\n      Everything in the process worked beautifully on my 5500 until I get to the login screen for GPE. Then I can successfully enter my password, but after about 10 seconds it comes back to the login screen.\n\n      I am assuming from the error messages below that I am unable to connect to the Xserver. I can’t see the sleep daemon causing the problem, and I’m not sure what the gtk error is. I can see that is Xfbdev is started with what looks to be goods options for collie. I am at a loss what to try next.\n\n      Thanks,\n\n      appended is my .xsesson-errors file\n\n      D-BUS per-session daemon address is: unix:path=/tmp/dbus-BkIKqrLsyc\n      stdin: is not a tty\n      Starting sleep daemon: ipaq-sleepmkdir: Cannot create directory `/var/run/no-sleep’: Permission denied\n\n      (gpe-login:1200): Gtk-CRITICAL **: gtk_container_add: assertion `GTK_IS_WIDGET (widget)’ failed\n      .\n      X connection to :0.0 broken (explicit kill or server shutdown).\n      X connection to :0.0 broken (explicit kill or server shutdown).\n   7. that_weasel Says:\n      May 2nd, 2005 at 12:42\n\n      I don’t have a Utilities, or GPE Group, and can’t seem to add one with the Laucher app. Anyone know why?\n   8. that_weasel Says:\n      May 2nd, 2005 at 13:07\n\n      Ok, I just realize that the Desktop entry file is for GPE. It’s not starting up for me….\n   9. antoniovf Says:\n      May 11th, 2005 at 00:00\n\n      Supose that you have conection to internet in the zaurus and have the packages in the compact flash instead of the openzaurus website. What does you write in the ipkg.conf file to read from the compact flash and not from internet? Thanks\n  10. bri3dd Says:\n      May 15th, 2005 at 18:26\n\n      antoniovf: do you have Packages files on the CF card(eg. you just used wget -r on the feed? If so just add like\n\n      src e /media/cf/feed/e/\n\n      and so on to\n\n      src x11 /media/cf/feed/x11/\n\n      onto the /etc/ipkg.conf.\n  11. lardman Says:\n      May 16th, 2005 at 15:52\n\n      @Ben Johnson:\n\n      Try removing keylaunch, this sorted the problem for me on my C750.\n\n      Either do this via ssh, or if you can’t get the connection up, log in as root and open the terminal, eventually (after being logged out a few times) the terminal will be left in front of the login screen and you can then proceed at your leisure.\n\n      Si\n  12. Olivier Berger Says:\n      June 18th, 2005 at 21:06\n\n      Just a quick note : I think that the doc referred to as http://www.openzaurus.org/oz_website/faq/faq?id=192 has moved actually to :\n      http://openzaurus.org/wordpress/howto/root-on-sd/\n\n      Regards,\n  13. alan Says:\n      June 28th, 2005 at 16:51\n\n      hi !\n      This how-to is wonderfull. It worked like a charm on my 750 : i installed GPE from a OPIE installation in the internal memory.\n\n      To do this, i just added this line to /etc.ipkg.conf :\n\n         dest home /home/packages\n\n      Then, i installed everything with :\n\n         ipkg -d home install .....\n\n      Of course, don’t forget :\n\n         Ipkg-link mount /home/packages/\n\n      Thanks to the writer of this how-to.\n      Best regards,\n      alan.\n  14. Archigos Says:\n      September 19th, 2005 at 17:14\n\n      I have a 5500 and tried this out… as far as I can tell it worked fine. I admit I’m not that good with Linux but was messing around in GPE fine. I SSH’d in and switched the VT back to 3 for Opie and created the “gotoopie” stuff from there. Not thinking I rebooted my Z and now it goes right to Opie.\n      How do I switch back to GPE (after reboot, or otherwise)?\n\n      After the reboot I switched to VT 2 (where I’m assuming GPE is) and all I see is text and cant do anything?\n  15. Archigos Says:\n      September 19th, 2005 at 17:16\n\n      Figured it out while messing with SSH… GPE is on VT 1.\n\n      WOO… Can I create something similar to the Goto-Opie deal for switching Opie2GPE?\n  16. DaddyGeek Says:\n      February 2nd, 2006 at 08:04\n\n      So how do I figure out which xserver is the appropriate one?\n      I am using an SL-C3000…','utf-8');
