INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (1992,'= Note to editors =\n\nTime to start writing it - I want to release 3.5.4.1 during this week - will protect page after release. \n\nUsers will be free to provide suggestions/addons via [[Talk:ReleaseNotes/Oz3541]] page - I will copy good content from there into page.\n\n----\n\nPlease split text into sections. Stuff common to many releases can be moved to separate pages.\n\nOld ReleaseNotes: http://oe.handhelds.org/cgi-bin/moin.cgi/OpenZaurusReleaseNotes - read it and copy content if needed.\n\n= Supported devices =\n\nThis release is available for the following \'\'machine families\'\' :\n\n[[c7x0]]  = c700, c750, c760, c860, sl-7500\n\n[[akita]] = sl-c1000\n\n[[spitz]] = sl-c3000, sl-c3100, sl-c3200\n\nNote that it is the first release of the 3.5.4 era for akita and spitz machines.\n\nUsers of other machines (collie, poodle, tosa) only need to install release 3.5.4 and/or apply upgrade feeds\' fixes for 3.5.4.\n\n\'\'Eric D:\'\' Please clarify this last paragraph. I take it to mean that earlier devices are no longer supported by new OpenZaurus releases, specifically that the new kernel and related core improvements (udev) won\'t be available on my collie. True?\n\n= Release Highlights =\n\n* [[ KernelInfo26 | Linux Kernel 2.6]] on all clamshell devices\n* altboot present, to allow booting from memory cards, etc.\n* Opie 1.2.1\n** TrueType fonts\n** Icons are properly scaled now\n** many hires fixes\n* GPE 2.7\n* WPA working out-of-box on Prism2 cards\n* Working extra buttons on all clamshell models (see [[KeyboardButtons]])\n* Working LCD hotkeys under GPE\n* The <tt>Power</tt> button now works as intended on SL-Cxx00\n* Improved keymaps for all models, USB keyboards now work out of the box\n* Bluetooth improvements all over the place, especially in the base system\n* Greatly enhanced auto-mounter for USB storage / SD / MMC / CF thanks to udev\n* Very fast suspend / resume cycles\n* e-image available, An X11-based distribution with the Enlightenment Window Manager\n* New cute OpenZaurus logo during boot (in GPE only ?)\n\n= Installation =\n\nInstallation is device specific - please see to [[Install|Install Guide]] for details.\n\n= 2.6 kernel notes =\n\nMany informations are provided on separate page: [[KernelInfo26|Kernel 2.6 Informations]]\n\n== all models ==\n\n* Sharp CE-RH1/CE-RH2 remotes does not work\n* sound is done by ALSA - use <tt>alsamixer</tt> in terminal to control it, or under GPE use the \"Audio Mixer\" application (<tt>gpe-mixer</tt>) found in \"Other\"\n* keyboard repeat is normal (was too fast in previous releases)\n* halt/reboot/poweroff works as should\n* use FN + <cursor-left> and FN + <cursor-right> to switch between console VTs (or back to OPIE/GPE)\n: not sure this works with GPE on akita :( -- it doesn\'t. --[[User:JTD|JTD]] 09:48, 2 June 2006 (BST)\n: This does not work on OPIE on spitz, either [[User:213.162.110.250|213.162.110.250]] 20:46, 4 June 2006 (BST)\n* Sharp camera card does not work and never will\n* Some SD/MMC cards results in I/O errors, timeouts - we work on it.\n* Green LED is used to show NAND Flash activity\n\n== SL-C7x0 ==\n\n* time can be lost on reboot\n* CPU Frequency change is supported via <tt>cpufreq</tt> - available are 100/200/300/400MHz settings (no overclocking)\n* Backlight range is increased (when compared to SharpROM)\n\n== SL-Cxx00 ==\n\n* USB Networking does not work with Microsoft Windows\n\n=== SL-C3x00 ===\n\n* SL-C3x00 does not use the flash partitions - the system boots straight off the HDD\n\n= Base system notes =\n\n* Images contains just a minimal timezone configuration (only for some subset of locations). If you need more then install the timezones package for your continent.\n\n= Opie notes =\n\n* The LCD hotkeys, and the space between are not supported yet\n* VT applet is removed from base install - install <tt>opie-vtapplet</tt> if you need it\n* Logout applet is removed from base install - install <tt>opie-logoutapplet</tt> if you need it\n\n= GPE notes =\n\n* All hotkeys (Calendar, Home, etc) should now be working as intended.<br>\n* The LCD hotkeys, and the space between are now fully functional, too.<br>\n* Default font-sizes on VGA devices with >=200DPI should now be actually readable.<br>\n\n= Enlightenment notes =\n\ntbd\n\n= Release Manager =\n\nMarcin \'Hrw\' Juszkiewicz','utf-8');
