he first boot may be quite long and some steps will not provide graphical output, so please be patient. The \"mail\" LED may flash when there is file system activity, which gives confidence on boot process state, but nothing very precise.\n\n== Links ==\n\nThis process is almost the same as the [[C7x0/Install|C7x0]] series.\n\nThis page was copied from http://openzaurus.org/wordpress/installation/sl-c1000/\n\n== Troubleshooting ==\n\n=== ln respawning too fast ===\n\nAn otherwise successful installation of 3.5.3 reboots and halts with this message:\n\n INIT: ld \"ln\" respawning too fast: disabled for 5 minutes\n\nMany other error messages could be seen flying by before halting with that one.\n\n; Solution:\n\nNo solution is known.  It appears that a number of critical files are missing.\n\n== Notes ==\n\n: Ensure that your C1000 machine has a standard flash partitioning (e.g. as it was originally), flashing may fail if this is not the case\n:: Does this mean that you can only flash once, because once you flash it changes the partitioning? --[[User:JTD|JTD]] 21:24, 10 May 2006 (BST)\n::: No. It uses same memory partitioning (see [[AkitaFlashPartioning]]) [[User:OlivierBerger|OlivierBerger]] 11:52, 25 May 2006 (BST)','utf-8');
