he first boot may be quite long and some steps will not provide graphical output, so please be patient. The \"mail\" LED may flash when there is file system activity, which gives confidence on boot process state, but nothing very precise.\n\n== Links ==\n\nThis process is almost the same as the [[C7x0/Install|C7x0]] series.\n\nThis page was copied from http://openzaurus.org/wordpress/installation/sl-c1000/\n\n== Troubleshooting ==\n\n=== ln respawning too fast ===\n\nAn otherwise successful installation of 3.5.3 reboots and halts with this message:\n\n INIT: ld \"ln\" respawning too fast: disabled for 5 minutes\n\nMany other error messages could be seen flying by before halting with that one.\n\n; Solution:\n\nNo solution is known.  It appears that a number of critical files are missing.\n\n== Notes ==\n\n: Ensure that your C1000 machine has a standard flash partitioning (e.g. as it was originally), flashing may fail if this is not the case\n:: Does this mean that you can only flash once, because once you flash it changes the partitioning? --[[User:JTD|JTD]] 21:24, 10 May 2006 (BST)\n::: No. It uses same memory partitioning (see [[AkitaFlashPartioning]]) [[User:OlivierBerger|OlivierBerger]] 11:52, 25 May 2006 (BST)\nIf you are flashing from a stock Sharp ROM, then your partitions are most likely OK for OZ, but if you have Cacko, then you will need to repartition before you can flash OZ.\n[[User:Menaie|Menaie]] 11:48, 17 June 2006 (AET)','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2042,'\'\'\'Location\'\'\': Sydney, Australia\n\ngot my first Zaurus (SL-C3000) on 14th March 2005\n\ngot second Zaurus (SL-C3100) on 21th September 2005\n\n\'\'\'Zaurus Accessories\'\'\':\nNetgear MA701 CF, SanDisk ConnectPlus 128 CF, Socket Bluetooth CF, 4GB Kingston CF, 1GB Transcend SD, 1GB SanDisk Exreme II USB plus SD, GoldX 5-in-1 USB cable, Avico USB Digital Camera Cord (OTG cable), iRiver USB host cable, USB LAN adaptors, aidata retractable rj-45 cables, Targus mini USB hub, Blue Eye powered mini USB Hub, BlueEye 40 GB 2.5\" USB HDDs, BlueEye 200 GB 3.5\" USB HDDs, BlueEye O2 80GB USB/Firewire HDD, mini USB mouse, mini USB keyboard, Belkin 4-in-1 stylus, Pilot Pentopia stylus, Joytech PSP power extender, Diatec P-Cord (P to Go), Sony PSP retractable Sync\'n\'Charge cable, OverLay Brilliant screen protectors,  Kairen USB VGA adaptor, dbTech USB CDRW/DVD\n\nI am primarily a Windows user, have been for many years, currently using W2K nd XP as my main OSes on all my desktop computers. Got one Libretto running as a Linux server so the Zaurus is my first Linux desktop/laptop/pda experience.\nstarted off using and customising the Sharp ROM and then tried out pdaXrom on C3000, now trying out OZ OPIE and GPE on C3000.\n\n\'\'\'Homepage\'\'\': http://zaurus.daemons.gr/menaie/','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2043,'Here you are open to add any suggestions to [[ReleaseNotes/Oz3541]] content. Please do it in this style:\n\n<hr />\nI think that OPIE part should have following info added:\n\n* something to add\n* something more to add\n\n* you mention about moving the Settings and Application directories for Sharp ROM. On the C1000 and C3x00 models, these directories are on /home/zaurus/Settings and /home/zaurus/Applications\n\n[[User:MarcinHrwJuszkiewicz|MarcinHrwJuszkiewicz]] 22:39, 16 June 2006 (BST)\n<hr />','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2044,'This describes how to install OpenZaurus on the [[Akita]].\n\nPrepare the image for flashing:\n\n# Download files: zImage.bin, initrd.bin, updater.sh. If the filenames are different, change them to the above or else the zaurus will not be able to find them. The filenames are somewhat case sensitive. Either use the capital I in zImage.bin, or all lower, or all caps.\n# Put files in the root directory of your CF or SD card (may be mounted in /mnt/cf in GNU/Linux, depending on your setup). The flasher program in the Zaurus asks you if you want to use CF or SD, so it is possible to use an SD instead of a CF card.\n\nThe steps to flash the C1000 from CF are(1):\n\n# Ensure that your C1000 machine has a standard flash partitioning (e.g. as it was originally), flashing may fail if this is not the case \n# Turn the zaurus over and flip the battery case switch to “Unlocked”. Remove the battery cover, and find the small reset microswitch on the left. The battery cover or the stylus can be used to press it.\n# Replace the battery cover and switch to “Locked”.\n# Insert the CF card with the image in the root, as described above.\n# Plug in the AC power jack. The yellow charge lamp must be on indicating external power, or you will get an error message in japanese later.\n# Press the “OK” key inside the round white arrow keys button, and keep it pressed while pressing the “On/Off” button on the front side.\n# The Maintenance Screen will display (in Japanese). Choose “Update” : this is item 4.\n# The next screen will ask the source, (1 - CF) and (2 - SD)\n# The next screen asks for confirmation, choose “Yes” this is the left button\n\nThe Zaurus will now erase the flash, write the new image, then reboot to your new Operating System\n\nNote that the flashing process does not erase your /home directory, therefore settings from other systems may remain there and possibly cause (sapace) problems\n\n(1)If flashing from SD, just replace CF with SD.\n\nThe first boot may be quite long and some steps will not provide graphical output, so please be patient. The \"mail\" LED may flash when there is file system activity, which gives confidence on boot process state, but nothing very precise.\n\n== Links ==\n\nThis process is almost the same as the [[C7x0/Install|C7x0]] series.\n\nThis page was copied from http://openzaurus.org/wordpress/installation/sl-c1000/\n\n== Troubleshooting ==\n\n=== ln respawning too fast ===\n\nAn otherwise successful installation of 3.5.3 reboots and halts with this message:\n\n INIT: ld \"ln\" respawning too fast: disabled for 5 minutes\n\nMany other error messages could be seen flying by before halting with that one.\n\n; Solution:\n\nTry 3.5.4.1-rc4\n\n* [http://ewi546.ewi.utwente.nl/tmp/hrw/3.5.4.1-test/rc4/images/akita/ download]\n* [http://openzaurus.org/wordpress/2006/05/22/fourth-release-candidate-of-openzaurus-3541/ announcement]\n* [http://www.oesf.org/forums/index.php?showtopic=18318 announcement forum thread]\n\n(This is being tested right now)\n\n== Notes ==\n\n: Ensure that your C1000 machine has a standard flash partitioning (e.g. as it was originally), flashing may fail if this is not the case\n:: Does this mean that you can only flash once, because once you flash it changes the partitioning? --[[User:JTD|JTD]] 21:24, 10 May 2006 (BST)\n::: No. It uses same memory partitioning (see [[AkitaFlashPartioning]]) [[User:OlivierBerger|OlivierBerger]] 11:52, 25 May 2006 (BST)\nIf you are flashing from a stock Sharp ROM, then your partitions are most likely OK for OZ, but if you have Cacko, then you will need to repartition before you can flash OZ.\n[[User:Menaie|Menaie]] 11:48, 17 June 2006 (AET)','utf-8');
