INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2066,'[[Install]] + [[Akita]] > Akita Installation\n\n----\n\n__TOC__\n\n This describes how to install OpenZaurus on the [[Akita]].\n\nThis process is almost the same as with the [[C7x0/Install|C7x0]] series.\n\n= Before You Begin =\n\n; Back up first!:\n\nIf you value any data on your device, back it up!\n\n(to do: link to the backup page)\n\n; Downloads:\n\nDownload these files:\n\n zImage.bin\n initrd.bin\n updater.sh\n\nIf the files you downloaded are named differently, <em>you must rename them so they match the above names.</em>\n\nThe filenames are somewhat case sensitive. Either use the capital I in zImage.bin, or all lower, or all caps.\n\n; Put them on a card:\n\nPut files in the root directory of your CF or SD card (may be mounted in /mnt/cf in GNU/Linux, depending on your setup). The flasher program in the Zaurus asks you if you want to use CF or SD, so it is possible to use an SD instead of a CF card.\n\n; Check partitioning:\n\n(to be completed)\n\nEnsure that your C1000 machine has a standard flash partitioning (e.g. as it was originally), flashing may fail if this is not the case.\n\nIf you are flashing from a stock Sharp ROM, then your partitions are most likely OK for OZ, but if you have Cacko, then you will need to repartition before you can flash OZ.\n\n(to be written: How does one repartition?)\n\n; Check your /home directory\n\nNote that the flashing process does not erase your /home directory, therefore settings from other systems may remain there and possibly cause (sapace) problems\n\n= Installing =\n\nThe steps to flash the C1000 from CF or SD are:\n\n# Turn the zaurus over and flip the battery case switch to \"Unlocked\". Remove the battery cover, and find the small reset microswitch on the left. The battery cover or the stylus can be used to press it.\n# Replace the battery cover and switch to \"Locked\".\n# Insert the CF card with the image in the root, as described above.\n# Plug in the AC power jack. The yellow charge lamp must be on indicating external power, or you will get an error message in japanese later.\n# Press the \"OK\" key inside the round white arrow keys button, and keep it pressed while pressing the \"On/Off\" button on the front side.\n# The Maintenance Screen will display (in Japanese). Choose 4 (\"Update\")\n# The next screen will ask the source (in English).  Choose 1 for CF and 2 for SD.\n# The next screen asks for confirmation, choose \"Yes\" this is the left button\n\nThe Zaurus will now erase the flash, write the new image, then reboot to your new Operating System\n\nThe first boot may be quite long and some steps will not provide graphical output, so please be patient. The \"mail\" LED may flash when there is file system activity, which gives confidence on boot process state, but nothing very precise.\n\n== Troubleshooting ==\n\n=== ln respawning too fast ===\n\nAn otherwise successful installation of 3.5.3 or 3.5.4.1-rc4 reboots and halts with this message:\n\n INIT: ld \"ln\" respawning too fast: disabled for 5 minutes\n\nMany other error messages could be seen flying by before halting with that one.\n\n; Solution: Perform a NAND restore and then re-attempt the installation.','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2067,'=== A Better Home Page ===\n\nIt would be nice to make our home page look more like http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Main_Page or [http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Main_Page]. -- [[User:Bronson|Bronson]] 16:49, 29 May 2006 (BST)\n\n=== Editing the Main Page ===\n\nHow would one edit contents of the Main page ? -- [[User:OlivierBerger|OlivierBerger]] 17:43, 28 May 2006 (BST)\n\n: This is the correct way to change any protected page: just use the discussion page.  If an admin isn\'t being responsive, try to contact hrw or lardman via IRC or contact me via email. [[User:Bronson|Bronson]] 16:24, 29 May 2006 (BST)\n\nMore specifically, I wanted to add some details : I think that the paragraph \'\'Device Families\'\' may be modified as follows:\n\nOpenZaurus runs on the following Sharp Zaurus devices, grouped by families corresponding to similar hardware characteristics :\n\n{|\n| [[Collie]] || [[Collie|SL-5000D, SL-5500]]\n|-\n| [[Poodle]] || [[Poodle|SL-5600]]\n|-\n| [[Tosa]] || [[Tosa|SL-6000]]\n|-\n| [[C7x0]] || [[C7x0|SL-C700, SL-C750, SL-C760, SL-C860, SL-7500]]\n|-\n| [[Akita]] || [[Akita|SL-C1000]]\n|-\n| [[Spitz]] || [[Spitz|SL-C3000 (spitz) , SL-C3100 (borzoi), SL-C3200 (terrier) ]]\n|}\n\nThat means for instance that owners of a borzoi machine (SL-C3100) will have to install an image of the \'\'Spitz\'\' family.\n\nWould it make more sense ? \n\n[[User:OlivierBerger|OlivierBerger]] 17:43, 28 May 2006 (BST)\n\n: It makes sense.  I\'ve updated the main page. -- [[User:Bronson|Bronson]] 16:24, 29 May 2006 (BST)\n\n== Installing on Spitz ==\n\nI\'ve written documentation on installing on Spitz/[[SL-C3000]].\n\n[[User:Sybren|Sybren]] 20:48, 12 June 2006 (BST)\n\n== Add \"about OpenZaurus\" ==\n\nCopy/migrate this content:\n\nhttp://openzaurus.org/wordpress/about/\n\nThe first thing I want to see when I visit a website/wiki/whatever is the answer to \"what is this place?\"\n\nThe history could be kept in another page, but a quick \"what is it, what\'s it for, what is this place\" type of note would be nice.\n\nAlso answer questions like.. Why OpenZaurus and not just GPE or Opie directly? would be nice to get answered.\n\n-- [[User:Sysy|Sy]] / <sup>[[User_Talk:Sysy|(talk)]]</sup> 16:28, 15 June 2006 (BST)\n\n== Fix rewriting ==\n\nRewriting isn\'t working perfectly.  An all-number title like [[3.5.4.1]] cannot be viewed directly. In the meantime I\'ll begin making an infrastructure like [[v3.5.4.1]]\n\nHmm, nevermind.  3.5.4.1 is IP-style and with newer versions of mediawiki it\'ll search for user contributions at that IP.\n\nEdit /.htaccess\n\n php_flag register_globals off\n RewriteEngine On\n RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f\n # MODIFIED RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d\n RewriteRule ^(.*)$ /index.php?title=$1 [L,QSA]\n\n: This is a much better technique than the old way (which I got off the MediaWiki wiki) of looking for a file extension.  Change made.  Thanks [[User:Sysy|Sy]]. [[User:72.74.131.205|72.74.131.205]] 17:40, 17 June 2006 (BST)\n\n== Enable subpages ==\n\n # Enable subpages in the main namespace:\n $wgNamespacesWithSubpages[0] = true;\n\nThis will allow [[sandbox]] and then visit that page and make [[/test]] which will automatically make [[sandbox/test]].  This is VERY useful for keeping things organized, especially release notes and discussion.\n\n: I never knew this option existed.  Again [[User:Sysy|Sy]], thanks.  [[User:72.74.131.205|72.74.131.205]] 17:40, 17 June 2006 (BST)','utf-8');
