INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2078,'Scott Bronson\n\nBoston, MA<br>\nFreenode: bronson<br>\nemail: <Email>bronson@rinspin.com</Email>\n\nHow I\'ve helped OZ: installed this wiki and help maintain it.  Also, a very long time ago I submitted a patch to fix the Opie Pacman game.  :)\n\n== Equipment ==\n\n* Zaurus [[SL-5500]] obtained through the [http://www.linuxdevices.com/news/NS4241298322.html Home Shopping Network blowout].\n* D-Link DCF-660W 802.11 Compact Flash card.\n* 256 MB SanDisk SD Card\n\n== Stupid Tricks ==\n\nIn case you need more swap for some task: http://www.denx.de/wiki/DULG/SwappingOverNFS\n\n== GPE Thoughts ==\n\nOpie is a far more polished environment.  That said, I like GPE better.  GPE feels somewhat like it\'s more a part of my desktop while Opie feels to me more like a one-off hack.  I expect that GPE will see more development in the future.\n\n[[Image:Port 2371.png|right]]\n\n* I\'ve seen a tiny analog clock in GPE screenshots.  Where can I obtain this?  The regular clock takes up too much valuable taskbar real estate and  problems with changing width and when the screen rotates/resizes.  This clock solves everything in one blow.  \n\nSome issues:\n\n* Why does a tap-longtap scroll a scroll bar to the extreme end?  This makes it damned hard to scroll line-by-line.  It\'s lika tap-tap-tap tap-damn where was I?  Its painful.  If I want to go to the bottom, I\'ll just drag the scroll bar thumb thank you very much.  (this awful behavior smells intentional because it seems like the device would have to go out of its way to do this...)\n\n* It\'s really strange that there\'s no active task switcher. I would expect a submenu in the Start menu or a task menu applet. Or both. Instead, you can sometimes click on the window\'s title bar.  How am I supposed to discover that??\n\n* Window titlebars take up a lot of room and really don\'t offer much functionality that I can tell.  The panel, on the other hand, is always overflowing with icons.  How about allowing us to place applets on the outsides of the window title bar?\n\n* interactive-help: useless, hopeless, a waste of space!\n** useless: couldn\'t find anything that actually offered help\n** hopeless: there is no way you\'re going to add help for everything that the user can click on.  It\'s much better\n** waste of space: the panel on a portrait Z doesn\'t have much room for icons.  And certainly it has no room for an icon this useless.\n** What\'s worse than not having a help button?  Having a help button that is totally and utterly unhelpful.\n\n* gpe-aerial:\n** Should take over the function of the wireless monitor.\n** Should display your current settings when you click on it\n** Shoulw have an \"associate with other networks\" button that would bring up the network switcher.\n\n* Panel doesn\'t handle rotation very well.  Especially the alarm clock changing its size.  Panel Manager should allow you to add and remove panel apps too.\n: Remove: just add an X right below the ^ and v arrows.\n: Add: make another list of the apps available to add.\n\n* Should add a battery graph to the CPU/mem monitor.  Ideally, whould make configurable which bars are shown in the panel.  Then the window that comes up would show all the bars, with labels.\n** network bandwidth\n** Disk space\n** temperature?\n\n* Package Manager\n** Should show progress monitor in dialog on startup.\n** Should quit entirely if startup window is closed.  As it is, it looks like it should work... but quits the minute you click on something.\n** Should display a description of the pack','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2079,'This page contains some guidelines to use when adding documentation to this site.  As long as pages follow these rules, we can maintain some consistency across the site.\n\n* It\'s \"Zauruses\", not Zaurii or other odd pluralizations.  \"Zaurus\" is always capitalized.\n* Always use [[DogName]]s unless you need to make a distinction of devices in the same family.  \'\'The [[Collie]] and [[Poodle]] are Portrait Zauruses.  Of these devices, the [[SL-5000]] and [[SL-5600]] have 32 MB of RAM while the [[SL-5500]] has 64 MB.\'\'\n* [[DogName]]s and [[Models|model names]] always redirect to the appropriate page.\n: Well... it\'s not obvious to do that since dognames are not wiki words (mix of upper/lower case)... so not specially easy to type when writing inn the wiki... --[[User:OlivierBerger|OlivierBerger]] 13:14, 13 April 2006 (BST)\n:: MediaWiki doesn\'t really use WikiWords anyway.  It requires <nowiki>[[brackets]]</nowiki> for each link.  -- [[User:Bronson|Bronson]] 18:48, 13 April 2006 (BST)\n\n* Use proper namespaces:\n** [[HowTos/Passwordless SSH]]\n** [[HowTos/Root on SD]]\n** [[Collie/Install]]\n** [[Poodle/Install]]\n\n* Use language code after section name:\n** [[HowTos/FR/Le réseau par USB]]\n** [[HowTos/DE/USB Netzwerk]]\n\n* The pages on this wiki should be used for professional, objective presentation of information.  Opinions and rants (within reason) are encouraged \'\'as long as\'\' they are on discussion pages or personal pages.  Create an account to obtain a personal page.\n\n* Edit early and edit often.  Pursue brevity and accuracy.  When a discussion winds down, replace it with a summary (just the conclusions, not a blow-by-blow).  When you make substantial edits, consider moving the original text to the Discussion page.\n\n== Transclusion ==\n\nOne problem with trying to organize OpenZaurus on a Wiki is that a large number of pages share small pieces of information.  For instance, you might want to include keymap information in both a device page and a kernel page but you don\'t want to duplicate this info all over the site because then changing it everywhere becomes a nightmare.\n\nTransclusion is the answer.  It allows you to include the content of a page WITHIN the content of any number of other pages.  When the transcluded page is updated, those changes are immediately reflected in all parent pages.  Here\'s an example that embeds the [[Template:TranslcudeExample]] page within within this page:\n\n{{TranslcudeExample}}\n\nSimply surround the name of the page you want to transclude in <nowiki>{{</nowiki>curly braces<nowiki>}}</nowiki>: <nowiki>{{</nowiki>[[Template:TranslcudeExample|TranslcudeExample]]<nowiki>}}</nowiki>.  All transcluded pages must live in the Template namespace.\n\n== Images ==\n\nWe now support images.  To upload an image, use [[Special:Upload|Upload file]] in the toolbox on the left.  Make sure to describe where the image came from and any copyrights that might apply.  To place an image on a page, use a tag like this: <nowiki>[[Image:</nowiki><i>name.png</i><nowiki>]]</nowiki>.  To float the image left or right, do this: <nowiki>[[Image:</nowiki><i>name.png</i>|right<nowiki>]]</nowiki>.\n\nSee the [http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Help:Images_and_other_uploaded_files MediaWiki help] for more.  We\'re running an [[Special:Version|older version]] of MediaWiki, however, so not every feature described on the help page will work on this wiki.\n\n= Links =\n\nAlso see [[using this Wiki]].','utf-8');
