INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2094,'This page describes how to write Wiki pages.  Follow the [[Style Guide]] if possible.   See [[Help:Contents]] for more general help.\n\n== Creating and Linking to Pages ==\n\nTo create a page you can add a link to it on an existing page, then click the link.  To create links, surround words with <nowiki>[[double brackets]]</nowiki>.  If pluralization gets in the way, letters can be moved outside the <nowiki>[[bracket]]s</nowiki>.  You can also completely change the text that <nowiki>[[brackets|gets displayed]]</nowiki>.  MediaWiki wiki does not automatically turn WikiWords into links.\n\nCreate subpages when possible.  For instance, to add a page to <nowiki>[[HowTos/Video]]</nowiki>, use <nowiki>[[/Divx]]</nowiki> instead of <nowiki>[[Divx]]</nowiki>.  This places the new content in HowTos/Video/Divx instead of just Divx.\n\n== Markup ==\n\nYou can use HTML as well as wiki markup.  For example, &lt;br&gt; inserts a line break.  \n\nUse &lt;nowiki&gt;...&lt;/nowiki&gt; to prevent text from being interpreted as wiki markup.  Use &lt;pre&gt;...&lt;/pre&gt; to preserve whitespace.  Easier than using pre, however, is just indenting the line:\n\n  Indented lines are presented like this.\n\n{| border=1\n|\n<nowiki>== New Section ==</nowiki><br>\n<nowiki>=== New Subsection ===</nowiki>\n\n|\n<h2>New Section\n<h3>New Subsection\n\n|-\n|\n<nowiki>\'\'Emphasize\'\', \'\'\'strongly\'\'\',</nowiki><br>\n<nowiki>\'\'\'\'\'very strongly\'\'\'\'\', &lt;tt&gt;typewriter&lt;/tt&gt;</nowiki><br>\n<nowiki><u>underline</u>, <strike>strikeout</strike></nowiki>\n\n|\n\'\'Emphasize\'\', \'\'\'strongly\'\'\',<br>\n\'\'\'\'\'very strongly\'\'\'\'\', <tt>typewriter</tt><br>\n<u>underline</u>, <strike>strikeout</strike>\n\n|-\n|\n<nowiki>* A bulleted list</nowiki><br>\n<nowiki>** A sub-item</nowiki>\n\n|\n* A bulleted list\n** A sub-item\n\n|-\n|\n<nowiki># A numbered list</nowiki><br>\n<nowiki>## A sub-item</nowiki>\n\n|\n# A numbered list\n## A sub-item\n\n|-\n|\n<nowiki>; Definition List : The Definition</nowiki>\n\n|\n; Definition List : The Definition\n\n|-\n|\n<nowiki>: indent a line</nowiki><br>\n<nowiki>sign a comment.  ~~~~</nowiki>\n\n|\n:indent a line\nsign a comment. [[User:Bronson|Bronson]] 20:43, 13 April 2006 (BST)\n|}\n\nSee the Wikipedia pages [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Editing Help:Editing] and [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Wiki_markup_examples Markup Examples] for more.\n\n== Transclusion ==\n\nOne problem with trying to organize OpenZaurus on a Wiki is that a large number of pages share small pieces of information.  For instance, you might want to include keymap information in both a device page and a kernel page but you don\'t want to duplicate this info all over the site because then changing it everywhere becomes a nightmare.\n\nTransclusion is the answer.  It allows you to include the content of a page WITHIN the content of any number of other pages.  When the transcluded page is updated, those changes are immediately reflected in all parent pages.  Here\'s an example that embeds the [[Template:TranslcudeExample]] page within within this page:\n\n{{TranslcudeExample}}\n\nSimply surround the name of the page you want to transclude in <nowiki>{{</nowiki>curly braces<nowiki>}}</nowiki>: <nowiki>{{</nowiki>[[Template:TranslcudeExample|TranslcudeExample]]<nowiki>}}</nowiki>.  All transcluded pages must live in the Template namespace.\n\n== Images ==\n\nWe support images.  To upload an image, use [[Special:Upload|Upload file]] in the toolbox on the left.  Make sure to describe where the image came from and any copyrights that might apply.  To place an image on a page, use a tag like this: <nowiki>[[Image:</nowiki><i>name.png</i><nowiki>]]</nowiki>.  To float the image left or right, do this: <nowiki>[[Image:</nowiki><i>name.png</i>|right<nowiki>]]</nowiki>.\n\nSee the [http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Help:Images_and_other_uploaded_files MediaWiki help] for more.  We\'re running an [[Special:Version|older version]] of MediaWiki, however, so not every feature described on the help page will work on this wiki.','utf-8');
