INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2162,'This page describes how to maintain the content on this site.\n\n= Editing Pages =\n\n[[Help:Editing|Editing Help]] shows some of the markup you can use.  You can experiment in [[Sandbox]].\n\n= Monitoring Pages =\n\nAn RSS feed reader is the best tool to use to monitor the entire site for changes.  Simply subscribe to [http://openzaurus.berlios.de/wiki/index.php?title=Special:Recentchanges&feed=rss this url].\n\nMediaWiki can email you whenever a page changes.  Just create an account, [[Special:Confirmemail|confirm]] your email address, and set up your watchlist preferences.  Your watchlist can include any page you have edited or just the pages you specify.\n\n= Controlling Spam =\n\nThe wiki currently allows unregistered users to edit the site in order to encourage more people to contribute content.  If spam becomes a problem we will be forced to make the site more restrictive.  As of 17 June 2005 this wiki has been up for 2 months and, except for some prescription drug spam links added in the first few weeks, we haven\'t had any spam trouble whatsoever.  Knock wood!\n\nWhen spammers hit the site, their changes are very easily reverted:\n* View the page\'s history\n* Click on the date of the page you\'d like to revert to.  This opens that revision in an edit window.\n* Ignore the warning about an out of date copy and save the page.  The spam has been eradicated.\n\n= Discussion =\n\nSimply type your comment and append <code><nowiki>~~~~</nowiki></code> to insert your name and the date (make sure you\'re logged in, of course).  There is no need to move one or two insightful comments to the discussion page.  However, once a discussion starts to distract from the content on a page, it needs to be moved to the discussion page.  Put a tiny summary and a link to the discussion page on the main page so that people know to look there for more information.\n\nRants are fine, but they need to be confined to discussion pages or personal pages.\n\nWhen you create an account, you are assigned a personal page.  Use this page to express your opinion, findings, whatever.  If it\'s not too offensive, add a link to the [[Users]] page so that others can find it.','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2163,'I haven\'t been able to finish the compilation because of sd IO errors\nbut the build process went far enough so that I\'m pretty confident it\'ll build the entire emacs\n(it stops somewhere in byte compilation of .el, I have even run a version of the emacs executable)\n\nI put this here if someone wants to give a try\n\n== pacakages to install:  (compilation with gtk toolkit)==\nipkg install :\ngcc-symlinks binutils-symlinks automake autoconf \nlibc6-dev gtk+-dev pkgconfig ncurses-dev libpng-dev libjpeg-dev \nlibungif-dev libx11-dev libxext-dev libxpm-dev libxft-dev libxrender-dev libxt-dev  \nmake xproto-dev libz-dev libungif4 diffutils		  \n\n** other packages are installed automatically as dependencies\n** tiff support is left out, x-extension also (xkb), no sound card support\n** note that  automake and autoconf are probably not  required...\n** not sure about if libxext-dev  libxft-dev libxrender-dev are required either;)\n\n== \"hack\" /usr/lib/libc.so :==\n<pre>\n/* GNU ld script\n   Use the shared library, but some functions are only in\n   the static library, so try that secondarily.  */\nOUTPUT_FORMAT(elf32-littlearm)\nGROUP ( /lib/libc.so.6 /usr/lib/libc_nonshared.a  )/*  /lib/ld-linux.so.2  )*/\n</pre>\n\n\n==./configure --with-gtk --prefix=/usr --without-xim ==\n==edit  src/config.h ==\n<pre>\n#define HAVE_XIM 0 \n</pre>\n(--witout-xim doesn\'t seem to have much effect...)\n\nand comment out:\n<pre>\n/* Define HAVE_X_I18N if we have usable i18n support.  */\n/*\n#ifdef HAVE_X11R6\n#define HAVE_X_I18N\n#elif defined HAVE_X11R5 && !defined X11R5_INHIBIT_I18N\n#define HAVE_X_I18N\n#endif\n */\n\n/* Define HAVE_X11R6_XIM if we have usable X11R6-style XIM support.  */\n/*\n#if defined HAVE_X11R6 && !defined INHIBIT_X11R6_XIM\n#define HAVE_X11R6_XIM\n#endif\n */\n</pre>\n== optional: exit X or use a swap ==\nJust to be sure to have enough ram\n== make bootstrap ==\nand wait','utf-8');
