INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2338,'I now realize that putting the HowTos in a strict hierarchy is probably a mistake.  There is just too much information that can appear in different places.  We do need a few well-written HowTos, but most of the info that appears on this site is scattershot.  Therefore, I think we need to adopt wikipedia\'s categories.  You create a small page, add it to a category, and use categories for navigation.  Much easier to maintain than a hierarchy.\n\nNow...  what categories do we need?  MachineNames, HostOSes, Topics, ...? -- [[User:Bronson|Bronson]] 22:06, 12 July 2006 (BST)','utf-8');
