INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2347,'= Controlling Spam, Monitoring Changes, etc. =\n\nSee [[Help:Contents]].\n\n= Changing the Sidebar =\n\nTo change the always-visible navigation links, modify [[MediaWiki:Sidebar]].  See [[Help:Sidebar]] for more.  Only admins can edit the sidebar.  See [http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Help:User_rights wikimedia] for more information.\n\n= Permissions =\n\n[[Special:Makesysop]]\n\n[[Special:Userrights]]\n\nhttp://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Help:User_rights\n\n= TODO =\n\n* Setup automatic backups for the database and the site repo.  (what about uploaded images?)\n* Test image upload.  This is fairly low priority but might be useful.  Screenshot galleries would be especially nice.\n* Show how to set up mirrors that use svk.  This way, if the database gets corrupted, you can just roll back time until you find a good version.\n* We should probably use categories to help organize things on this site: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Category\n\nmuch later:\n\n* Ask someone to create a custom theme.  [http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/MediaWiki_look_and_feel] [http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Skins]  Look to [http://hula-project.org] or [http://www.mono-project.com/Main_Page] for inspiration.  Ensure that the new theme is easily read on Zaruses (even 240 pix wide?)\n\n= Done =\n[[Template:Admin/Done]]:\n{{Template:Admin/Done}}\n\n= Tools =\n\n[[ShowTimestamp]]\n\n= Statistics =\n\n[http://openzaurus.berlios.de/usage/ Site Statistics]\n\n[https://www.google.com/analytics/home/report?rid=554045 Google Analytics]\n\n[http://openzaurus.berlios.de/info.php PHPInfo]','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2348,'<noinclude>\n\'\'This page contains the Wiki-related news items from the Wiki\'s front page.  To add a news item to the front page, add it immediately after this noinclude section.\'\'\n</noinclude>\n\n\'\'\'2006-06-17:\'\'\'\n\nThe [[ReleaseNotes/Oz3541|3.5.4.1 release]] is still being [[http://openzaurus.org/wordpress/2006/06/17/oz-3541-status-update/ fine-tuned]].\n\nWe now support [[Help:Editing#Images|image upload.]] Bring on the screenshots! Also, thanks to a configuration change suggested by [[User:Sysy|Sy]], it\'s now possible to use periods in page names on this Wiki.\n\n\'\'\'2006-06-03:\'\'\'\n\nThe 3.5.4.1 release is still being prepared. Expect it in a matter of days.\n\nWe now have mirrors! Use one whenever the BerliOS site is slow. If you can, please help out by setting one up. It\'s easy.\n\nYou can now access this wiki using the easy-to-remember http://wiki.openzaurus.org\n\n\'\'\'2006-06-01:\'\'\'\n\nThe 3.5.4.1 release is still being prepared. Expect it in a matter of days.\n\nWe now support only the MonoBook skin. If you want to use another skin to view this wiki, contact me.\n\nYou can now access this wiki using the easy-to-remember http://wiki.openzaurus.org\n\n\'\'\'2006-05-25:\'\'\'\n\nThings are still quiet on the Wiki while the the 3.5.4.1 release is prepared.\n\nAll the old content has been moved into this Wiki. Thank you to everybody who helped out! Please contribute by organizing and expanding the documentation on this site. Or, create your user page to tell what OZ-related hardware and software you\'re using.\n\n\'\'\'2006-05-19:\'\'\'\n\nThings are quiet on the Wiki while the the 3.5.4.1 release is prepared.\n\nThere are still a few documents that have yet to be copied from http://openzaurus.org into the wiki. Please help out by finding one and moving it over. You could also create your user page to tell what OZ hardware and software you\'re using.\n\n\'\'\'2006-04-25:\'\'\'\n\nThis wiki is fairly new! Please help out by copying existing documentation from http://openzaurus.org into the wiki.\n\nBerliOS had a rather catastrophic outage last week that knocked this site offline. We\'ve now ensured that this site is backed up daily and will soon establish a read-only mirror so that the effect will be less painful should another outage occur.\n\n\'\'\'2006-04-14:\'\'\'\n\nThis wiki is brand new!  It went live on the morning of Friday 14 April 2006 so there\'s not much content yet. This wiki should eventually become the canonical location for OpenZaurus documentation. Please help out by:\n** Copying existing documentation from http://openzaurus.org into the wiki.\n** Creating an account and tting up a user page that tells the OZ hardware and software you\'re using.','utf-8');
INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2349,'Just some random thoughts...  Organization is currently breaking down and I\'d like to somehow fix it.\n\nI now realize that putting the HowTos in a strict hierarchy is probably a mistake.  There is just too much information that can appear in different places.  We do need a few well-written HowTos, but most of the info that appears on this site is scattershot.  Therefore, I think we need to adopt wikipedia\'s categories.  You create a small page, add it to a category, and use categories for navigation.  Much easier to maintain than a hierarchy.\n\nNow...  what categories do we need?  MachineNames, HostOSes, Topics, ...? -- [[User:Bronson|Bronson]] 22:06, 12 July 2006 (BST)\n\nIn fact, pretty much every page on this site is a howto.  Even the installation instructions tell how to install oz.  The only exception I can think of offhand are the machine pages, [[Collie]], [[Spitz]], etc.  So what sense is there in stuffing everything under /HowTo?','utf-8');
