INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2353,'Just some random thoughts...  Organization is currently breaking down and I\'d like to somehow fix it.\n\nI now realize that putting the HowTos in a strict hierarchy is probably a mistake.  There is just too much information that can appear in different places.  We do need a few well-written HowTos, but most of the info that appears on this site is scattershot.  Therefore, I think we need to adopt wikipedia\'s categories.  You create a small page, add it to a category, and use categories for navigation.  Much easier to maintain than a hierarchy.\n\nNow...  what categories do we need?  MachineNames, HostOSes, Topics, ...?\n\nIn fact, pretty much every page on this site is a howto.  Even the installation instructions tell how to install oz.  The only exception I can think of offhand are the machine pages, [[Collie]], [[Spitz]], etc.  So what sense is there in stuffing everything under /HowTo?\n\nAnd really, there\'s basically no difference between a long FAQ entry and a short HOWTO.  In fact, I think there\'s even overlap.  I wonder if the FAQ and short HOWTOs should be merged somehow.','utf-8');
