INSERT INTO mw_text VALUES (2409,'=== Hints And Tips ===\n\n\'\'GPE\'\'\n\n<tt>Here are some ideas for enhancing/changing the GPE interface. Please add to the list any that you\'ve found:\n\nBeing able to use the LCD softkeys and the space between them is great. I\'ve mapped the space below the Book icon to toggle hiding the panel. Being able to hide the panel is useful, but trying to bring it back can be difficult sometimes, so in /etc/keylaunchrc.matchbox I\'ve modified the following line:\n\n<tt>key=....F30:-:~matchbox-remote -panel-toggle</tt>\n\nDoing a lot of command line typing I get tired of the shift+\"/\" to get the slash. I use it much more than I use commas so I modified the /etc/keymap-2.6.map so it\'s the comma that requires the shift:\n\n<tt>keycode  51 = slash  comma</tt>\n\nSpice up the prompt with a bit of color, by changing the PS1 statement The code below will create white brackets around red text that has shows username@hostname:current directory. So this will work best with a dark background, don\'t use it if you\'ve got a white background:\n\n<tt>PS1=\'\\[\\033[1;37m\\][\\[\\033[1;32m\\]\\[\\033[1;31m\\]\\u@\\h:\\w\\[\\033[1;37m\\]] # \\[\\033[0;0m\\]\'</tt>\n\nTo change the default colors of the Rxvt terminal, edit the .Xdefaults file in your home directory. Black background with green text would look like:\n\n<tt>Rxvt*background: black</tt>\n\n<tt>Rxvt*foreground: green</tt>\n\nIf you don\'t want the matchbox panel switching to the right hand side of the screen on rotation, edit /etc/matchbox/session and add --no-flip the matchbox-panel command:\n\n<tt>matchbox-panel --orientation south --no-flip &</tt>','utf-8');
